column12: Various folders of items belonging to collections and several items placed in folders. These might have come from Vicky Jones' office--just not sure. But it's clear that some work has been done on this material--for example, there are some call numbers written on pieces and some pieces have been encapsulated. I got this box from Marilyn Reaves, I think when she retired. I looked through the box and it is various items that will go into existing collections. I put some sticky-notes on some of the folders indicating collections, but that was just a quick pass-through. It appears to be a hodge-podge of material. I'm sorry I don't know more about provenance. Sort of related: I did have some individual manuscript material that resulted from a purge of the donor files to rid them of actual collection material; these materials had been stored with Marilyn in record storage boxes as well but came to me at her retirement. I went through that material during the initial pandemic period to determine placement. My hope is that this RSB is the last of stray manuscript material like that, though I may find some individual pieces here and there in my office.

column12: Walter Smart attended the World Fantasy Convention in Seattle in 1989. Ursula Le Guin was a speaker at several sessions. Walter asked Ursula for permission to record her, which he did on S-VHS magnetic tapes. He later transferred these to DVD to give to us for our collections. Following archival theory and practice, these DVDs should be made into their own small collection, produced by Smart, rather than being added to the Le Guin Papers.
